OL,5, Car manufacturers appear split on the  
OL,6, decision by the government to delay the
OL,7, ban on new petrol and diesel car sales.
OL,9,FPrime Minister Rishi Sunak confirmed   
OL,10,Fthe planned ban was being pushed back  
OL,11,Ffive years from 2030 to 2035.          
OL,13,FHe said it was "not right to impose    
OL,14,Fmore costs on working people", adding  
OL,15,F"sensible green leadership" was needed.
OL,17,FFord said the move undermined its      
OL,18,Felectric car investment plans, but     
OL,19,FToyota welcomed the announcement,      
OL,20,Fsaying the delay was "pragmatic".      
